  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: e9620f8c34305754d8cc9a7e49e852d9, type: 3}
  m_Name: Tutorials_en
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Unity.Localization::UnityEngine.Localization.Tables.StringTable
  m_LocaleId:
    m_Code: en
  m_SharedData: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 5610f14d3a062b2418043ec61248b6c3, type: 2}
  m_Metadata:
    m_Items: []
  m_TableData:
  - m_Id: 1425946595328
    m_Localized: The pieces will be positioned in a way that the opponent's King
      is stalemate, with a highlight on the square where it is located. You will
      need to choose one of the pieces from the options and then position it to attack
      the King, delivering checkmate.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1426005315584
    m_Localized: One piece will be in the center of the board. You will need to choose
      the correct starting square(s).
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1426005315585
    m_Localized: One of the squares will be highlighted. You will need to choose
      the name of the square from the options.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1426005315586
    m_Localized: 'The pieces will be positioned, and the opponent''s King will be
      highlighted. You will need to state its current situation: check, checkmate,
      stalemate, or safe.'
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1426005315587
    m_Localized: A mystery piece will be positioned on the board, with the possible
      squares circled. You will need to identify this piece.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1426005315588
    m_Localized: Your opponent will have positioned their pieces in highlighted positions.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1426005315589
    m_Localized: You will position your pieces according to the number of coins available
      for the phase and the cost of each piece.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  - m_Id: 1426005315590
    m_Localized: Your opponent's pieces will be revealed. You and your opponent will
      capture each other's pieces until one of you gains the necessary point advantage.
    m_Metadata:
      m_Items: []
  references:
    version: 2
    RefIds: []
